article.description: Zach Jackson scored 25 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Omaha to an 84-71 win over Montana State on Thursday night.
article.headline: Jackson scores 25 points, leads Omaha past Montana St. 84-71
article.linkText: Jackson scores 25 points, leads Omaha past Montana St. 84-71
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- Zach Jackson scored 25 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Omaha to an 84-71 win over Montana State on Thursday night. Omaha (4-11), which has won three of its last four games, opened the season with an 89-80 overtime loss to the Bobcats. The Mavericks closed the first period on a 23-10 run to lead 41-28 at the break. Montana State never threatened in the second half. Jackson was 6 of 7 from the floor, with three treys, for 15 points and six rebounds in the first half. He finished 9 of 11 on field-goal attempts. JT Gibson added 18 points while dishing out four assists and Matt Pile chipped in 10 points for Omaha, which shot 59 percent (31-53) from the floor while limiting Montana State to 26-of-71 (37 percent) shooting. Harald Frey had 20 points for Montana State (7-6). Joe Mvuezolo Jr. had 16 points and Keljin Blevins added 12 with 10 rebounds.
